# Shell scripts must always be checked out with LF line endings,
# regardless of core.autocrlf on the checking-out machine. A CRLF shebang
# line ("#!/bin/sh\r\n") makes the kernel look for a nonexistent
# "/bin/sh\r" interpreter - confirmed to break a Docker image built from a
# Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true (container exits immediately
# with "exec: line 8: ./start.sh: not found"), even though the exact same
# file works fine wherever it wasn't converted, like the VPS itself.
*.sh text eol=lf
